Course.create(title: 'LAWW 6503.  International Externship  (Irregular).  3 Hours.', description: 'The International Externship exposes students to the manner in which academic learning in areas such as international law and transnational legal transactions is implemented in practice, with opportunities to observe and evaluate the strategies and effectiveness of attorneys in their representation of clients in international and transnational legal practice, to improve legal research and writing skills, and to consider and resolve issues of professional responsibility in an international context. Duties in an IE may include work on assigned cases and transactions, research, preparation of memoranda, consultation with attorneys and members of courts and governmental agencies, observation and discussion of legal proceedings, and attending conferences with counsel when feasible and when such conferences are conducted by the Field Supervisor or another attorney associated with the Field Supervisor. A student extern must engage in at least 168 hours in placement-related assignments during the externship term. Completion of Professional Responsibility is preferred. Additional requirements may be imposed to suit the placement. Placements contemplated within this externship include international public interest organizations and law firms, etc. Placements may be located domestically or abroad.', coreqDesc: '', coreqData: '{ "Course0": []}', prereqDesc: '', prereqData: '{ "Course0": []}')
